<title>USA: Pretty Good Privacy acquires Zoomit Corp.</title>
<headline>Pretty Good Privacy acquires Zoomit Corp.</headline>
<dateline>SAN MATEO, Calif. 1997-03-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Internet secutiry firm Pretty Good Privacy Inc on Monday said it has acquired Zoomit Corp, a Toronto-based developer of the Internet directory technology.</p>
<p>Terms were not disclosed.</p>
<p>PGP said the deal would link its data scrambling software, also known as encryption software, and Zoomit's directory technology to provide information security and information access for businesses.</p>
<p>Zoomit's Meta-directory software enables organizations to integrate employee and company data into existing directories, and determine which individuals and groups have access to the information.</p>
